<bioghist encodinganalog="545"><head>History of Xavier University Athletic Advisory Board</head><p>The Board has been known by various names in the course of its history. Its earliest title seems to have been The Athletic Council. It existed under that name as early as 1923. In 1935, as a result of Xavier's loss of North Central Association accreditation over the football program, the Athletic Council was abolished and replaced by the Board of Athletic Control, also referred to as the Athletic Advisory Council. By the 1970's it was simply called the Athletic Board. More recently it has been called the Athletic Advisory Board.</p><bioghist><p>Not specified</p></bioghist></bioghist><scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a"><head>Scope and Content</head><p>Meeting minutes, correspondence and related documents of the Xavier Athletic Advisory Board.</p><scopecontent><p>Not specified</p></scopecontent></scopecontent><arrangement encodinganalog="351$b"><head>Statement of Arrangement</head><p>Materials are arranged in this general manner:</p><list type="marked"><item>Meeting agenda, minutes and related documents arranged chronologically</item><item>Board correspondence arranged chronologically</item><item>Documents relating to the men's basketball coach search of 1979</item></list></arrangement><accessrestrict encodinganalog="506"><head>Restrictions on Access</head><p>Restricted access.Please contact the Xavier University Archives staff.</p></accessrestrict><prefercite encodinganalog="524"><head>Preferred Citation</head><p>Box Number, Folder Number, XUA-16, Athletic Advisory Board minutes and related documents,Special Collections and Archives, Xavier University Library, Cincinnati, Ohio.</p></prefercite><controlaccess><head>Indexing Terms</head><p>The following terms have been used to index the description of this collection in the library's online public access catalog.</p><controlaccess><head>Organizations/Corporations:</head><corpname encodinganalog="610$a" source="lcsh">Xavi